

✅ HttpMessage (Base Class)

	Fields: headers, body

	Methods:

		get_header(key)

		set_header(key, value)

		has_header(key)

		content_length()


✅ HttpRequest : inherits HttpMessage
	
 	Fields: method, uri, http_version, query_string

	Methods:

		parse_request_line(line)

		get_method()

✅ HttpResponse : inherits HttpMessage

	Fields: status_code, reason_phrase

	Methods:

		set_status(code, reason)

		build() → returns full HTTP response as a string



✅ HttpParser
	Handles incremental parsing of an HTTP request

	Fields: state, buffer, request

	ethods:

		feed(data)

		is_complete()

		get_request()


✅ HeaderMap (used internally by HttpMessage)
		Essentially a case-insensitive map

		Wraps std::unordered_map<std::string, std::string>